    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="533"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/3–2448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Italy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 24, 1948—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>819. Murray and Carey indicate willingness send 2 or 3 sound Ital speaking <gloss
                        target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss> trade union leaders to discuss <gloss
                        target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> with Ital trade unionists<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d533fn1">In the convention of the <gloss target="#t_CIO1"
                            >CIO</gloss> at Boston in 1947 Secretary Marshall spoke, emphasizing the
                        need for aiding the countries of Europe and following the address the <gloss
                            target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss> unanimously adopted a foreign policy
                        resolution embodying the principles stated by Marshall.</note> but believe
                    visit prior to elections might be resented Ital labor and play into Communist
                    hands. They think visit after election preferable.</p>
                <p>Dept feels that split away of <gloss target="#t_CGIL1">CGIL</gloss> minority and
                    formation non-Communist trade union center will inevitably occur as in France
                    since Communists will almost certainly call strikes designed cripple Ital
                    economy and <gloss target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> if they lose election. We
                    indicated to Murray and Carey they can help materially if disposed to encourage
                        <gloss target="#t_CGIL1">CGIL</gloss> minority breakaway and give moral
                    support and financial aid.<note n="2" xml:id="d533fn2">In Dunn’s press telegram
                        1378, March 27, not printed, it was reported that <hi rend="italic"
                            >Popolo</hi> (Christian Democratic) and <hi rend="italic">Umanità</hi>
                        (Saragat Socialist) reported Carey’s declaration that the Communist version
                        of the conversations with him in London were grossly false. <hi
                            rend="italic">Unità</hi> (Communist) and <hi rend="italic">Avanti</hi>
                        (Nenni Socialist) did not mention the report. (840.50
                        Recovery/3–2748)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Carey and to some extent Murray still seem reluctant take active steps in this
                    direction but <gloss target="#t_AFL1">AFL</gloss> will cooperate fully in any
                    such effort.</p>
                <p>Will you evaluate possibility and timing of <gloss target="#t_CGIL1">CGIL</gloss>
                    split; advise us whether <gloss target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss>–<gloss
                        target="#t_AFL1">AFL</gloss> visit would be useful and best time for such
                    visit. Invitation to <gloss target="#t_AFL1">AFL</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss> should we think come from <gloss
                        target="#t_CGIL1">CGIL</gloss> minority on basis of relations already
                    established at London <gloss target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
